wikipedia_page.main: Florence Barker (23 March 1908 – 1986) was a competitive swimmer who represented Great Britain at the 1924 Summer Olympics in Paris, where she won a silver medal as a member of the second-place British women's team in the 4×100-metre freestyle relay event.  In individual competition, she advanced to the semi-finals of the women's 100-metre freestyle event, finishing ninth overall.
